text: Bainsla or Baisla is a clan of Gurjar ethnic community. It's variant spellings include Bainsle, Baisle Besle, Bansla and Bansal. ==Ethnography== They are generally located in northern Indian states of Rajasthan, Madhya Pradesh, Haryana, Punjab, Himachal Pradesh, Delhi and Uttar Pradesh. most of their population found in these states. ==Notable people== * Kirori Singh Bainsla == References == Category:Gurjar clans Category:Social groups of Rajasthan Category:Social groups of Haryana
title: Bainsla
